description: The British street artist Banksy has been busy in all the boroughs during his one-month “residency” in New York.
title: Banksy in New York
title_page: Banksy in New York - The New York Times
maintext:
Slide 1 of 10,
Posing under a mid-October installation in Brooklyn by the British street artist Banksy. The anonymous Banksy, whose anti-establishment stencils have sold for as much as $2 million, has spent October in “residence” in New York City, turning out virtually a piece a day.
